# What NOT to upload to Vercel.
#
# Vercel's CLI (and the build's working-tree snapshot) reads this
# first; falls back to .gitignore if absent. .gitignore alone isn't
# reliable here because Vercel doesn't honor every nested pattern,
# so we restate the bulky exclusions explicitly. Listing things that
# are already in .gitignore is intentional (defense in depth).

# Build artifacts & dependencies — rebuilt by Vercel on the deploy side
node_modules
.next
out
build

# Local + sibling-tool metadata
.git
.vercel
.claude

# Editor / OS noise
.DS_Store
*.tsbuildinfo
next-env.d.ts

# Env files (Vercel uses its own env-var system; never ship secrets in the upload)
.env*

# Repo-root scratch — these directories should never reach the deploy
# even by accident. The Team Photos/ folder is an untracked Google Drive
# export at the repo root; the originals subdirs are the multi-GB raw
# photographer dumps kept on disk for re-curation (see decision #66).
/Team Photos/
/public/photos/originals/SLOHS Sports Photographs-part-*/

# Docs — readable on GitHub; no need to ship to the runtime
/docs
